State of the art, current Intel GPU bring-up frontier
======================================================

This file is a raw proof transcript.  Read it like the HDA log: every line
claims one hardware boundary and does not claim the next boundary.

Current proven claims in this capture:

- `pci-claim`: TrueOS claimed Intel GPU `00:02.0`, device `0x4680`,
  revision `0x0C`, with `0x1000000` bytes of MMIO.
- `guc-proof`: GuC firmware was found and bootstrap reached
  `bootrom=JUMP_PASSED`, `ukernel=READY`, `auth=0x2`.
- `display-proof`: primary boot surface is on `pipe-a`, live surface register
  matches `0x02000000`, and the logo path reports `ok=1`.
- `vertex-upload-proof`: CPU writes the canonical three-vertex triangle,
  reads back the exact bytes, and flushes the upload range before submit.
- `mi-scanout-store-proof`: RCS wrote one DWORD into the exact live scanout
  surface and CPU readback saw the commanded value.
- `post-draw-light-sync-proof`: `vf-streamout-proof`, `vf-draw-path`, and
  `ps-launch-big-primitive` all report `post3d_light_marker=1` while
  `final_after_light_marker=0`, `post3d_marker=0`, and `final_marker=0`.
- `pc-retire-triad-proof`: `postdraw-light-only-retire` reports
  `light_cs_stall=1 before_light=1 post3d_light=1 final_after_light=0`, while
  `postdraw-pc-postsync-no-cs` reports `accepted=1 light_cs_stall=0
  before_light=1 post3d_light=0 final_after_light=1 final=1`.
- `vf-proof`: `vf-streamout-proof`, `vf-draw-path`,
  `vs-draw-frontier`, and `vs-streamout-proof` report
  `vf-proof accepted=1` with IA counters moving.
- `clip-raster-proof`: `vf-draw-path` reports
  `clip-raster-proof accepted=1` with `cl_delta=1`, `cl_prim_delta=1`.
- `ps-launch-frontier-proof`: on `vf-draw-path` and
  `ps-launch-big-primitive`, the PS launch input frontier reports
  `input_ready=1` while PS/CPS/depth counters all remain zero; both paths now
  also show `post_draw_light=1 post_draw_final_after_light=0`.
- `vs-proof`: `vs-draw-frontier` and `vs-streamout-proof` report
  `vs-proof accepted=1` with `vs_delta=3`, and shader upload matches the baked
  blob.
- Current negative frontier: the draw reaches a light post-3D `PIPE_CONTROL`
  post-sync write only when `CS_STALL` is set, but that combination blocks the
  following plain MI store.  Removing `CS_STALL` lets the command tail retire
  but loses the PC post-sync write.  The oversized VF primitive proves a
  full-surface coverage candidate, but `fragment_observed=0` and the PS
  spectrum remains gated.

